# Copy to `.env.local` (gitignored) for local dev, and set the same value as a
# GitHub Actions secret named VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID for production builds.
#
# OAuth 2.0 "Web application" client ID from Google Cloud Console, used by the
# Google Identity Services (GIS) token client for the Google Calendar integration.
# Authorized JavaScript origins must include http://localhost:5173 (Vite dev) and
# your production origin. Leave the OAuth consent screen in "testing" mode and add
# yourself as a test user. Required scopes:
#   https://www.googleapis.com/auth/calendar.calendarlist.readonly
#   https://www.googleapis.com/auth/calendar.events
#
# When unset, the calendar OAuth UI shows a "not configured" note (non-fatal).
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
